According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Low-Altitude UAVs Market was valued at USD 8.9 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 9.6 billion in 2025 to USD 15.4 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 8.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust expansion as unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) operating below 1,000 meters become increasingly essential across industries including agriculture, logistics, infrastructure inspection, mapping, surveillance, emergency response, and urban mobility. Continuous advancements in autonomous navigation, artificial intelligence (AI), battery technology, and beyond visual line of sight (BVLOS) capabilities are enabling broader commercial adoption, while supportive government regulations and investments in drone infrastructure are accelerating market growth worldwide.
